ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: If you're really into Chemistry then I would recommend this class to another student. The class was interesting but went more in depth into Chemistry than I was originally anticipating.

ENAS 648 is an environmental fate and transport class, relying heavily on organic chemistry. If the student were legitimately interested in the fate of chemicals in the environment, and proficient in environmental chemistry, then yes I would.
This course is really helpful when we intend to understand the basic theories of contaminants' transport in the environment.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: This course was essentially an introduction to the entire field of environmental organic chemistry, which was useful for me.
